{
  "id": 5109852273377280,
  "name": "Element-scoped view transitions",
  "summary": "Exposes element.startViewTransition() on arbitrary HTML elements.  The element establishes a scope for the transition, which means that the transition pseudo-elements are affected by ancestor clips and transforms, and multiple transitions on separate elements can run concurrently.",
